description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exciting new role opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced administrator who enjoys working as part of a busy multi-organisational team?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Discharge Liaison team is changing to respond to the increasing needs of the local community and support discharge pathways for patients with complex needs and improved pathways during the COVID-19 pandemic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Team works to facilitate rapid, seamless discharges back to the patient’s home or into the community. You will work closely with the discharge coordinators; medical and nursing teams to ensure patients are discharged as soon as they are medically fit and will be key in supporting the Trusts length of stay and patient flow programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a service delivery administration lead to work alongside the management team in optimising service performance, identifying any delays or gaps in the system, and supporting improvements. The role will also lead the team of administrators, ensuring the quality and accuracy of the information flows are maintained.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 18th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lynn Sanders Integrated Discharge Team Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;lynn.sanders1@nhs.net  01737768511 ext 2515&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alternative contact-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Beth Choate Discharge Team Lead Bleep 727&lt;/p&gt;
